#1502
Stealth: Silent Ascension~
   The guildmaster glances around carefully to ensure you're alone before
leaning in to say, 'You've come to the attention of the Thieves Guild, and I do
mean that in the best way. I know the Guild does not officially exist, so we'll
speak no further of that, but it has taken a keen interest in you nonetheless.'
   The guildmaster slips you an iron coin. You glance at it before sliding it
into your pocket, but it appears blank.
   'The Guild greatly anticipates your legacy among the shadows, but would like
to see your prowess firsthand. If you wish to ascend in its esteem, do so by
accepting this task: you will pickpocket, without being caught, no fewer than
50 times. And let us be clear: It cannot be from your own citizens, who might
be disarmed by a familiar face. These must be strangers. Lastly, aid the Guild
until you make contact with its agent in the Tower Skycleave, and help him bug
the Grand High Sorcerer's office. Do all this, and return to any master of the
Guild.'
   The tasks set before you are thus:
   1. Master the Stealth skill,
   2. Reach level 100,
   3. Pickpocket 50 people who are not members of your empire, and
   4. Aid the Guild by placing a bug in the Grand High Sorcerer's office in
      the Tower Skycleave
~
   The guildmaster silently and covertly takes the iron coin back from you. No
words are exchanged, but the two of you have an understanding. Your name shall
go unknown, but your deeds will be legend among the shadows.
~
